cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a function space approach to representation learning and analyzes the representation layers in deep learning architectures. This is a core topic in machine learning and hence, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper discusses the analysis of feature space clustering in deep learning architectures, which is a common problem in computer vision and pattern recognition. Hence, cs.CV is also a likely sub-category.
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper deals with deep learning architectures and their representation layers, which are a part of neural computing. Hence, cs.NE is another likely sub-category.
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach to representation learning, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely sub-category.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the Besov smoothness index, which is a measure of the geometry of clustering in the feature space. This is related to information theory and hence, cs.IT is a possible sub-category.
